        <div class="main-questions">
        <h3> What is Explorers</h3>
        <!-- This text is a summary from https://www.scouts.org.uk/explorers/ and the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/  -->
        <p> Explorers are a group of young people aged <b>14 to 18.</b> </p>
        <p> Our programme aims to be fun and challenging activities that develop skills, confidence, leadership and characer - by joining with frinends to do new things</p>
        <hr> 
        <h3> When and where? </h3>
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <p> We normally meet on Mondays from 19:45 to 21:30, this can change from week to week</p>
        <p> But this is communicated to Parents and explorers through email, a couple days before</p>
        <p> We normally meet at St Columba's Church Black Hall, for inside activities, and Ravelston. Follow the buttons below for google maps direction. </p>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/snRJqXYHawTrtXhS6" alt="church direction"><button type="button">St Columba's Church</button></a>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/ZnZ1731y8SDsADCXA" alt="ravelston park"><button type="button">Ravelston Park</button></a> 
        <hr> 
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> What area do we cover? </h3>
        <p> We cover Davidson' Mains, Blackgall, Comely Bank, Criagleith Hill, Stockbridge, Murrayfield and Crewe Toll</p>
        <p> If you are unsure whether we cover you area, please send us a message through the <a href="contact.html">contact us page </a></p>
        <hr>
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> What is the cost, and how do I pay it? </h3>
        <p> The cost each term is £35.</p>
        <p> We use an online payment system, we send out an email before the start of each term letting you know when the subs are due. </p>
        <hr>
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> What are the subs used for?</h3>
        <p> This money covers our main costs which are capitation to the Scout Association (mainly for insurance for our activities),
            rental of the halls that we use, badges, materials and activities.
        </p>
        <hr>
          <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> Are there an additional charges?</h3>
        <p> Where we undertake significant activities off-site we may need to make an aiddtional charge.</p>
        <p> The costs of camps and other nights away, is an additional cost for those who take part.</p>
        <hr>
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> Is there a Uniform, and how do I get one?</h3>
        <p>Pink Panthers' uniform is an Explorer Scout Shirt and a black and pink unit necker.</p>
        <p>Neckers will be provided by us, but we ask for £5 to cover the cost.</p>
        <p> The shirts can be purchased from the Guide Shop at 16 Coates Cresent, or can be order through the Glasgow Scout Shop. These are linked below.</p>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/JQfJWLjsozP943aE7"><button type="button">Guide Shop</button></a>
        <a href="https://www.glasgowscoutshop.com/"><button type="button"> Glasgow Scout Shop</button></a>
        <hr> 
        <!-- This text is taken from the current home page of http://www.pinkpanthersexplorers.org.uk/ -->
        <h3> Where do I put badges on my Uniform?</h3>
        <p> Please refer to the diagram linked below for where to put badges.</p>
        <a href="https://homesitecmsblobdev.blob.core.windows.net/imagecache/4/0/4/1/9/c/40419c0be9f25052882accd3c37bba086f8c64cb.png"><button type="button">Explorer Scout Uniform Diagram</button></a>
